Reasoning: The paper focuses on the quantitative analysis of users' behavior on Facebook with respect to misinformation and rumor spreading. This involves the use of data mining and machine learning techniques to analyze large datasets, which falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Security and Privacy (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of functional illiteracy and information overload on the formation of public opinion, which could be related to the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY). The analysis of users' response to different types of information, including troll contents and debunking attempts, could also be relevant to the sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
